{{for|the Marrano victim of the Inquisition|Juan de la Abadia}}
[[File:Juan de la Abadia - Saint Sebastian.jpg|thumb|200px|''San Sebastián'', Madrid, Museo Lázaro Galdiano after the painting of the Saviour, Museum of Zaragoza.]]
'''Juan de la Abadía el Viejo''' ([[floruit|fl.]] 1470-1498, probable death 1498) was a Spanish painter in the [[Gothic art|gothic]] Spanish-Flemish style. His son, '''Juan de la Abadía el Joven''', worked with him after 1490. 

His known works include Santa Catalina (1490) in the church of la Magdalena de [[Huesca]], now lost, the Saviour from the hermitage of [[Broto]], now at the [[Museum of Zaragoza]] and the Santo Domingo in [[Almudévar]] (Huesca), after which he was known as the '''Maestro de Almudévar''' until identified by the art historian Ricardo del Arco.<ref>[http://www.museodelprado.es/enciclopedia/enciclopedia-on-line/voz/abadia-el-viejo-juan-de-la/ Biografía en la enciclopedia online del Museo del Prado]</ref>

